"Overall:  classic.  Still remember my introduction to this beer:  2006 and my (now) mother-in-law would buy it for trips up to the North Shore of Lake Superior.   I was completely smitten and obsessed.  Since then a lot of hoppiness happiness has come into existence, but this is still a great beer, at least if you get it fairly fresh (...I've had bottles that are approx 3 month old, and they have been shadows of the real thing.)  Quite often, anymore, the melon notes really stand out to me and that is less than ideal, and definitely not the kind of bitterness I love.  Still, I find the flavor and mouthful profile to be fairly unique: I can pick it out, blind, when compared with almost any other IPA I've tasted."
