"Pours a light shade of copper, with a dull haze. Dense head of one and a half fingers, stubborn lacing and great retention. The smell of whole hop cones are very apprent in the nose, fruity and herbal, with a hint of pine. Toasted amber malt and a slight ester begin the flavor, and a citrus/pine alpha-oil hop aftertaste balances the taste without drying it out. Light carbonation and medium body allow an uncommonly smooth mouthfeel for a I.P.A.; bitter without becoming harsh. Finishes with residual light caramel and a pleasent hop bite, an excellent drinkability."
